    <text>
        <front/>
        <body>
            <pb n="3" facs="#f0001"/>
            <div n="1">
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="#b">Interesting Correspondence with M. Alex.<lb break="yes"/>de Humboldt.</hi>
                </head>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>
                    <hi rendition="#c">From the Courier and Enquirer.</hi>
                </p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>The Ocean Steam Navigation Company of this<lb break="yes"/>city having determined to call the third and fourth<lb break="yes"/>steamers of their line the Franklin and the Hum-<lb break="no"/>boldt, authorized their President, Mr. <hi rendition="#k">Sand</hi>, to in-<lb break="no"/>form M. <hi rendition="#k" >de Humboldt</hi> of their intention, and beg<lb break="yes"/>his sanction to giving his name to one of their ships.<lb break="yes"/>The letter was forwarded to Berlin through the me-<lb break="no"/>dium of the Prussian Minister at Washington, M.<lb break="yes"/>
                    <hi rendition="#k">de Gerolt</hi>, and by the last arrival, the President of<lb break="yes"/>the Company was favored with M. <hi rendition="#k">de Humboldt&#x2019;s</hi>
                    <lb break="yes"/>reply, through the medium of Mr. <hi rendition="#k" >Donelson</hi>, our<lb break="yes"/>Minister at Berlin.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>We have the pleasure of laying before our read-<lb break="no"/>ers a translation of this letter, containing so pleas-<lb break="no"/>ing an expression of the generous sentiments of one<lb break="yes"/>of the greatest spirits of the age: &#x2014;</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>
                    <hi rendition="#i">To</hi> C. H. <hi rendition="#k">Sand</hi>, Esq, <hi rendition="#i">President of the Ocean Steam Nav.<lb break="yes"/>Company, New York:</hi>
                </p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>
                    <hi rendition="#k">Mr. President</hi>&#x2014;Through the medium of my old<lb break="yes"/>friend, Mr. de Gerolt, our Minister in the United<lb break="yes"/>States, I have to-day&#x2014;while occupied with the pre-<lb break="no"/>parations for a journey to Paris&#x2014;received the friend-<lb break="no"/>ly letter, dated 21st August, with which you have<lb break="yes" />been pleased to honor me. It informs me that a fa-<lb break="no"/>vor has just been conferred on me, of which I could<lb break="yes"/>not believe myself worthy, of associating my name<lb break="yes"/>with that of a great citizen, who, from my earliest<lb break="yes"/>youth, has been the object of my liveliest admira-<lb break="no"/>tion. I venture to request you, sir, to present the<lb break="yes"/>homage of my respectful acknowledgements to the<lb break="yes"/>gentlemen directors of the Ocean Steam Navigation<lb break="yes"/>Co., who, on the flattering motion of Mr. Stephens,<lb break="yes"/>have determined that the fourth ship of their line of<lb break="yes"/>mail steamers between New York and Bremen shall<lb break="yes" />bear my name.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>In rendering you, Mr. President, the interpreter<lb break="yes"/>of my sentiments, you will be pleased to accept the<lb break="yes"/>expression of my gratitude due to your kind co-ope-<lb break="no"/>ration, and the delicacy of your proceedings. De-<lb break="no"/>voted as I am, by my travels and labors to the noble<lb break="yes"/>destinies of the new continent, and taking the most<lb break="yes"/>lively interest in the most direct and closest com-<lb break="no"/>mercial intercourse between the United States and<lb break="yes" />my country, I put the highest value on the honor<lb break="yes"/>which you confer upon me in the decline of a life<lb break="yes"/>which has had no other merit than that of a courage-<lb break="no"/>ous perseverance in the love <choice><sic>of a</sic><corr type="editorial">for the</corr></choice> good and freedom<lb break="yes"/>of opinion.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <cb/>
                <p>
                    <hi rendition="#i">Berlin.</hi>
                </p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <cb/>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I have the honor to remain,<lb break="yes"/>With the highest consideration,<lb break="yes"/>Sir, your ob&#x2019;t humble servant,<lb break="yes"/>ALEX. DE HUMBOLDT.</salute>
                </closer>
            </div>
            <lb break="yes"/>
        </body>
